description:
When Sonic Hedgehog and his sibling, Manic Hedgehog and Sonia Hedgehog go to the supermarket with their mother Queen Aleena, they all want to get different types of cereal, but to their dismay, their mother says they can only choose one. Just how much will the triplets go through just to make sure they get their favorite cereal? Watch and find out.

Directed by:
Tamers12345

Screenplay by:
Tamers12345 & Knuckles the Echidna

Produced by: 
Sonic the Hedgehog & Knuckles the Echidna

Executive Producers:
Tamers12345 & Bartleby Montclair of Dresdin

Production Designer:
Sonia the Hedgehog

Editor:
Charles the Hedgehog

Hair and Makeup by:
Mindy Latour & Mark Latour

Costume Design by:
Aleena the Hedgehog

Co Producer:
Manic the Hedgehog

-----------------------------------
Well, it's finally done! It always feels so good when I get done with a full on animated video. Please comment and let me know what you think of this, because I poured all my blood, sweat, and tears to get this bitch done!

comments.text: To anyone watching, please, this kind of thing does NOT represent the Sonic fandom at all. We Sonic fans are nothing like this person and find his work just as bizarre as you do. With help from voice actors from the animation community Sonic Paradox (responsible for the Sonic Shorts, which have poked fun at this type of video), I personally created Sonic the Other Movie and Xonic S, both intelligently written parody series with not a crack ship or sexualized animal between them. Those are the kinds of things normal Sonic fans like, not this.
comments.author: Kyoko Soryu

comments.text:
You don't actually believe this is real and serious do you? 
Also, I used to like Sonic Paradox when I was a massive Sonic fan back when I was like 10, but looking at Sonic Paradoxs stuff now is just mostly cringeworthy.
comments.author: lemmingscanfly5

comments.text:
Early Sonic Shorts are cringeworthy because basically anything was accepted. Regardless of the shorts, I'm talking about stuff like Metropolis Mayhem and associated works like Sonic F. Those are not cringeworthy by any means (although episodes 3 and on of F are substantially better than the first 2)).

The TL;DR of the rest of this comment is that this is definitely not a troll.

I have decent reason to believe this is legitimate. Not only is it way too subtle to be a troll, and this guy has so many videos and a dA account full of art and stories. I couldn't believe it was real at first either, but I dug through all his stuff and it is totally consistent. A troll wouldn't write and draw the same exact Bartleby x Sonic sub-dom stuff over and over without making it more and more shocking each time, but it makes perfect sense for somebody who actually gets off on it to do so. The fact that you do think he's a troll shows you haven't seen enough trolls and bad but legitimate fanwork to tell the pretty massive differences between them.

I've been in the Sonic community for well over a decade (Sonic Paradox did not exist when I  was ten) and I've seen my fair share of real disturbing and artificial disturbing. Every time friends within the fandom find something like this we eat it up, and if it's a fic we'll do a Skype call and read it. I can tell you this does not look artificial. Trolls always try way too hard to be as shocking as possible, and none of them would ever put this much effort into a cheap laugh. If this video were a troll video I can guarantee you it would not even be half as long, not paced appallingly slowly and way filthier. Honestly it'd actually be sadder if this was a troll putting this much time and energy into creating the most believably creepy 13 year old ever.
